’Щ@8c07b824386bd31198771d039bec3773c7a63b88d80415b0ee3e6d36e71c4f7cЪЇTitle: title: bits and
Path: Examples
Content:
Apply bitwise and to two numbers
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 2 | bits and 2
2

```
Apply bitwise and to two binary values
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 0x[ab cd] | bits and 0x[99 99]
Length: 2 (0x2) bytes | null_char printable whitespace ascii_other non_ascii
00000000:   89 89                                                Г—Г—


```
Apply bitwise and to a list of numbers
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [4 3 2] | bits and 2
в•­в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”¬в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•®
в”‚ 0 в”‚ 0 в”‚
в”‚ 1 в”‚ 2 в”‚
в”‚ 2 в”‚ 2 в”‚
в•°в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”ґв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•Ї


```
Apply bitwise and to a list of binary data
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> [0x[7f ff] 0x[ff f0]] | bits and 0x[99 99]
в•­в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”¬в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•®
в”‚ 0 в”‚ [25, 153]  в”‚
в”‚ 1 в”‚ [153, 144] в”‚
в•°в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”ґв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•Ї


```
Apply bitwise and to binary data of varying lengths with specified endianness
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 0x[c0 ff ee] | bits and 0x[ff] --endian big
Length: 3 (0x3) bytes | null_char printable whitespace ascii_other non_ascii
00000000:   00 00 ee                                             00Г—


```
Apply bitwise and to input binary data smaller than the operand
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 0x[ff] | bits and 0x[12 34 56] --endian little
Length: 3 (0x3) bytes | null_char printable whitespace ascii_other non_ascii
00000000:   12 00 00                                             вЂў00


```
